    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 6th level, your attacks in beast form count as magical for the purpose of overcoming resistance and immunity to nonmagical attacks and damage.</p><p>Additionally, whenever you assume a Wild Shape form, you can imbue the form with elemental power. Choose one of the following damage types: acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder; while in this form you have resistance to the chosen damage type and once per turn when you hit a target with your form's Bestial Strikes, you may expend a spell slot to enhance the attack with bonus damage of the chosen type. The extra damage is 1d8 per level of spell slot expended.</p>",
